The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Gujarat glorious

 Gujarat State Sangeet Natak Academy and Gujarat Lalit Kala Academy, in association with Anjika and Open Doors, present Gujarat Darpan, a five-day festival showcasing Gujarat in all its splendour. Being inaugurated this evening at 5 by governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi, it opens with an exhibition of paintings by Ravi Shankar Rawal at Gallery Sanskriti, Alipore (till November 27). Beginning tomorrow, Bishaka Shome Lakhia will display the traditional arts of kalamkari and block-printing at Weavers Studio, 10.30 am. An array of Gujarati crafts and cuisine, along with performances of bhavai dance await the audience at Swabhumi, 5.30 pm onwards (till November 27). A colourful extravaganza of Gujarati folk dances is on the cards at Tollygunge Club (November 25, 7.30 pm). Mrs Moorthy, an English play (dir: Varun N Maira), will be enacted on November 26 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar, 6.30 pm. On the 27th, the festival agenda includes classical dance recitals by Maulik Shah and Ishira Parekh (Kathak) and Rema Shrikant (Bharata Natyam) at G.D. Birla Sabhagar, 6.30 pm, as also folk dances at EZCC, Salt Lake, 6.30 pm. The final day?s programme features Ek Chhabili Paanch Chhabila, a Gujarati play by Raju Shukla (G.D. Birla Sabhagar, 6.30 pm) and classical dances at EZCC, Salt Lake, 6.30 pm.

 Event: A festival showcasing the splendour of Gujarat

 When: November 24 - 28




